--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This role manages sshpass.

Tool for non-interactively performing password authentication with so called
"interactive keyboard password authentication" of SSH. Most users should use
more secure public key authentication of SSH instead.

For more detailed information on the usage and available configuration options
please consult the following sections.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
USAGE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

INSTALL
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: sshpass
       sshpass_state: 'install'

REMOVE
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: sshpass
       sshpass_state: 'remove'

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
VARIABLES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ROLE
  sshpass_state
    Specify predetermined 'sshpass_state' variable (string).

    Install: 'true' | 'yes' | 'install'
    Remove : 'false' | 'no' | 'remove'
    Default: 'install'

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DEPENDENCIES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

PACKAGES
  sshpass: >= 1.05
    RedHat, CentOS, Gentoo

